headline: Investing.com’s stocks of the week
summary: Investing.com – U.S. equities were extremely volatile this week, as investor concerns regarding valuations led to declines, especially among technology stocks. However, there were some names that managed to make solid gains.

headline: Expedia Group (EXPE) Is Up 17.4% After Raising Revenue Outlook on Strong Q3 Results
summary: Expedia Group reported strong third-quarter 2025 results, posting US$4.41 billion in sales and US$959 million in net income, and raised its full-year revenue guidance to 6%-7% growth, up from the previous 3%-5% range. The company also declared a US$0.40 per share quarterly dividend and highlighted continued double-digit growth in both bookings and B2B operations compared to the prior year. Given management's upgraded outlook, we'll consider how this guidance increase influences Expedia...
